The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Sept. 10: Sebis primary market advisory committee today discussed a proposal to reduce the time taken to list shares after a public issue closes to five days. At present, it takes about 15 days to allot the shares and seven more to list the company on the bourses.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 10: The contraction in price index was lower at (-) 0.12 per cent for the week ended August 29 from (-) 0.21 on higher prices of milk, cereals, pulses, fruits and vegetables.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 10: The government will divest about 5 per cent of its stake in power firm NTPC by the end of this financial year. It is for the government to decide. The stake dilution will be 4.75 per cent to 5 per cent, NTPC chairman R.S. Sharma said.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 10: The account maintenance charges of the proposed low-cost pension scheme will be reduced to provide safety to people in the unorganised sector, interim regulator PFRDA said.                                                                                                                           
